[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    35[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mBAA posture is explicit: "AWS BAA signed. Every service listed is HIPAA-eligible under the BAA when configured correctly. See the [AWS HIPAA Eligible Services reference]." The link points to the canonical AWS reference, not an invented URL.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    36[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m Encryption coverage is complete across every PHI-bearing store. S3 SSE-KMS with customer-managed keys; DynamoDB encryption at rest with customer-managed KMS; SageMaker KMS on processing volumes, model artifacts, and Feature Store offline/online stores; Redshift KMS cluster encryption; TLS in transit everywhere. The Feature Store online-store specific KMS callout is correct.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    37[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m IAM is least-privilege per role with concrete examples: "Glue aggregation role: [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140ms3:GetObject[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m on claims-parquet, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140ms3:PutObject[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m on features-parquet, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140msagemaker:PutFeatureStoreRecord[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m. Scoring role: [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140ms3:GetObject[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m on features-parquet, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140ms3:PutObject[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m on anomaly-signals, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mdynamodb:GetItem[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m on provider-peer-groups. Case assembly Lambda: [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140ms3:GetObject[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m on anomaly-signals, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mathena:StartQueryExecution[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m for evidence pull, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mdynamodb:PutItem[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m on case-registry. Outcome Lambda: [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mdynamodb:UpdateItem[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m on case-registry, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140ms3:PutObject[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m on labels-parquet. No [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140m*[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m actions in production." Same scope-every-action-to-specific-resource-ARNs discipline that Chapter 2, Recipe 3.1, and Recipe 3.2 settled on.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    38[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m CloudTrail data events on the case-registry, provider-peer-groups, labels-parquet, and claims-parquet are required, with the explicit framing "Audit trail for every signal computation, every case creation, and every investigation outcome." This is the audit-trail discipline a HIPAA auditor and a payment integrity SIU investigator actually use.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    39[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m Retention posture is correct and substantive: "HIPAA baseline is 6 years for records containing PHI. Investigation outcomes have additional retention requirements under some state laws and anti-fraud regulations (often 7-10 years). Coordinate with legal and compliance on the specific retention schedule for your jurisdictions." This is the right operational guidance for the multi-regime retention reality of payment integrity records.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    40[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m Synthetic data discipline is explicit. Synthea is named with a verified GitHub link, CMS aggregate provider utilization files are referenced as a development-only resource with the specific caveat that "they cannot substitute for provider-level transactional data," and "Never use real PHI in development" is stated. The HTML-comment TODOs acknowledging that direct aws-samples repos for healthcare payment integrity have not been confirmed are the correct discipline; the recipe does not invent URLs to fill the gap.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    41[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m Data Access Controls row is substantive: "Case records and claims evidence contain provider PII and patient PHI. Access restricted to the payment integrity team; all reads and writes logged; no broad read grants on the case registry table." This is the right access-boundary discipline for a system whose unit of analysis is the provider rather than the claim.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    42[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The "Why This Isn't Production-Ready" section's "Data retention is complicated" bullet correctly acknowledges the multi-regime retention reality (HIPAA 6-year baseline, state insurance law overlays often longer, audit-log specific rules) and the right operational discipline ("Coordinate with the records management team on a per-data-type retention schedule rather than using a single global policy").[K
