[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    56[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Prerequisites Fairness Monitoring Data row ("Subgroup dashboards require provider-level attributes that may not be in the claims warehouse: practice size, patient-population demographics, geographic characteristics. Coordinate with provider-network operations on what attributes are available and how they can be joined to the case registry."); Step 5 [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mretrain_supervised_quarterly[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m subgroup evaluation block ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140msubgroup_metrics = { "specialty": ..., "peer_group": ..., "region": ... }[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m); "Why This Isn't Production-Ready" Subgroup Fairness Monitoring bullet.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    57[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly identifies that subgroup performance evaluation requires access to provider-level attributes (practice size, patient-population demographics, geographic characteristics). It correctly defers the "what data is captured" question to the provider-network operations team and the health-equity team. But the architectural artifacts that make subgroup monitoring binding rather than aspirational are not specified: where the demographic-and-attribute store lives, who has read access, how it joins to predictions and case records, what the audit trail for subgroup queries looks like, and what IAM scope the training job role and the QuickSight dashboard role need on the demographic data.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    58[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    59[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mProvider-network attributes that proxy for patient demographics (e.g., the patient mix of providers serving Medicaid populations, providers in rural health clinics, providers in FQHCs) have different governance from PHI in some regulatory regimes; some state insurance regulators restrict secondary use of network-tier and patient-population data more tightly than HIPAA restricts PHI per se. The retrain query as written has direct access to all subgroup attributes ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mspecialty[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mpeer_group_key[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mregion[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m) and produces subgroup metrics in the training output, which means the training job role implicitly needs read access to those attributes. That's not currently in the IAM section, and the QuickSight dashboard's subgroup view should query an aggregated subgroup-metrics table (not the raw demographic-joined case-registry archive) so that dashboard users don't get row-level demographic visibility. Same finding shape as Recipe 3.2 S2.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    60[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Add a "Subgroup data access" row or paragraph to Prerequisites: "Subgroup performance evaluation requires read access to provider-level attributes (practice setting, geographic region, patient-population demographics where captured, network tier). These attributes may be governed differently from claims PHI in some regulatory regimes; restrict read access to the demographic-and-attribute store to the training job role and the QuickSight dashboard role, and audit subgroup queries via CloudTrail data events. The QuickSight dashboard backed by Athena should query an aggregated subgroup-metrics table, not the raw demographic-joined case-registry archive, so dashboard-user access does not require row-level read on the subgroup attributes." Strengthen the IAM row with the per-role scope: training job role gets [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mglue:GetTable[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m and [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140ms3:GetObject[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m only on the demographic-joined view; QuickSight dashboard role gets read-only on the aggregated subgroup-metrics table.[K
