[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    118[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m3[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe "shift from 99213 to 99214" canonical example needs the temporal caveat.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe's most-quotable upcoding example ("the urgent care in the suburbs where the distribution of evaluation and management levels went from a reasonable-looking bell curve centered at 99213 (level 3) to a distribution that leans almost entirely on 99214 and 99215 (levels 4 and 5)") is correct as a pattern-recognition example but should acknowledge that the same shift, if observed across the entire peer group during 2021-Q1, is legitimate documentation-rule alignment rather than upcoding. The peer-group comparison naturally normalizes this (everyone shifted together, so the relative z-scores stay stable), but the self-CUSUM detector will fire on every provider during the transition window.[K
