[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    198[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m1[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mKernel SHAP[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m (model-agnostic). Works on any prediction function. Computationally expensive (typically 30 seconds to several minutes per prediction at the per-feature contribution level), which is impractical at scale for tens of thousands of provider-period scores per month.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    199[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    200[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m2[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mPath-length attribution.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m A custom attribution that computes per-feature contributions to the path length, derived from the original Liu/Ting/Zhou Isolation Forest paper. Implementations exist in research code but are not in the SHAP library directly.[K
