[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    438[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mFinding A1 is the only HIGH finding and is editorially small but materially important. The 2021 CMS/AMA E/M overhaul affected nearly every U.S. outpatient provider simultaneously and produced a distributional shift in the exact direction the recipe presents as the canonical upcoding pattern. The recipe's domain authority depends on getting this right. The fix is three coordinated edits to the main recipe plus a corresponding update to the Python companion's [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mEM_CODES[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m dictionary; a single editorial pass on both files closes the gap.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    439[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    440[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mFinding A2 is the now-recurring trigger-idempotency pattern. With this finding flagged across nine consecutive recipes (2.4-2.10, 3.1, 3.2, 3.3), the cookbook would benefit substantially from a shared appendix that covers the patterns once (S3 events with conditional DynamoDB writes, EventBridge bus → Lambda async with deterministic event keys, EventBridge Scheduler with deterministic Step Functions execution names, Kinesis with idempotent consumers, SQS with deduplication tokens). Each subsequent recipe could reference the appendix rather than repeat the discipline. A trigger-idempotency appendix is now the highest-leverage cookbook-wide editorial investment.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    441[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    442[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mFinding S1 is the now-recurring PHI-minimization-inside-the-BAA pattern, with the fourth distinct surface across the cookbook (Chapter 2: serialized prompt context; Recipe 3.1: examiner free-text reasoning; Recipe 3.2: patient-facing reminder content; Recipe 3.3: internal SNS notification payload). A cookbook-wide PHI-minimization appendix would consolidate all four surfaces with one teaching pass.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    443[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    444[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe Honest Take section is publication-ready and should be preserved verbatim in any editorial pass except for the V2 fix (the LLM-narrative aside). The seven-paragraph structure (feature engineering matters more than the model, peer group definition is the most consequential design decision, the operational cost of false positives is worse than you think, the narrative summary is surprisingly important, the Isolation Forest catches things z-scores don't, don't-build-supervised-first, don't-let-the-system-drive-toward-maximize-cases) is the kind of operations-engineer voice the cookbook is built on. The closing trap warning ("If you measure the system by cases generated, you incentivize lowering the thresholds and producing more noise. If you measure it by precision-weighted recovery, you incentivize fewer, better cases") lands the right final tone.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    445[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    446[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe Thursday-afternoon vignette is the densest payment-integrity writing in the cookbook to date and should not be shortened. The "142,000 claims," "18,000 billing providers," "40 cases per analyst per month," and the five behavioral-drift examples (CCM expansion, PT four-code regimen, HCPCS G0299 unit-rounding, modifier 59 at 42%, lab CPT-mix shift) are the specificity that establishes the recipe's authority. Each behavioral-drift example maps to a real billing scenario any payment integrity director would recognize, and CPT codes are correctly cited throughout (97110/97112/97140/97530 for PT; 99490 for CCM; G0299 for RN per 15 minutes). The only stale CPT in the recipe is the implicit 99201 reference in the new-patient level 1 bucket of Step 1's E[38;2;191;97;106m&[38;2;191;97;106mM distribution, which Finding A1 addresses.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    447[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    448[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe fairness section is substantive and the framing-level treatment ("an anomaly flag is a prompt for a conversation with the provider, not an accusation") is exactly the operational reframing this domain needs. The architectural artifacts that make subgroup monitoring binding (Finding S2) are the right operational backstop.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    449[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    450[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe risk profile of this recipe is similar to Recipes 3.1 and 3.2 (no LLM in the core path, no clinical-recommendation surface, no FDA exposure). The financial-and-operational stakes are real (provider relationship damage from false positives, recoverable-dollar leakage from false negatives) but bounded by the recipe's own framing. The Chapter 2 "validation-retry safety bypass" pattern that has dominated those reviews does not apply here.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    451[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    452[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mStyle hygiene is exceptionally clean: zero em dashes (direct U+2014 character check), zero en dashes in narrative prose (the 8 detected en dash matches are inside ASCII-art box-drawing characters in the architecture diagram, not in prose). No marketing language, no documentation-voice. The 70/30 vendor balance is preserved cleanly.[K
