[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    455[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    456[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mCoordinate with the existing code review ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mreviews/chapter03.03-code-review.md[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m). The code review PASSed-with-reservations on three WARNINGs in the Python companion. The code review's Finding 5 (CPT 99201 deleted from CPT in 2021) is upstream-related to A1 in this expert review; if A1 is fixed in the main recipe, the Python companion's [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mEM_CODES[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m update happens naturally in the same coordinated pass. The code review's Finding 7 (no validator on outcome event payload) is a separate concern from A2 (trigger idempotency) but both should be addressed in the outcome-joiner Lambda in the same editorial pass. The code review's Finding 6 (Key vs Attr in FilterExpression and pagination) connects to A5 (case-lineage discipline): a Step 4.5 implementation should use Attr correctly and paginate.[K
