[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     32[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mClaims and clinical data describe the same encounter through different lenses.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The claims data is structured around the billable transaction (one inpatient stay produces three to twenty claims). The clinical data is structured around the encounter (one inpatient stay is one encounter). The linkage pipeline's job is to produce a useful join despite the disagreement, not to "fix" either side.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     33[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe matcher runs in batch but is event-aware.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Unlike recipe 5.5's query-time matcher, claims-to-clinical linkage runs in batch over a sliding window (typically the past 90 to 180 days). Within the window, the linker re-evaluates as new claims arrive and as EHR encounters get amended.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     34[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mCluster-then-link is the right ordering.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Match each claim individually and you lose the structural information that several claims belong to the same encounter cluster. The demo follows this discipline.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     35[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mDate tolerance is encounter-class-specific.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Inpatient claims need a wide tolerance covering the entire stay plus the late-billing window; outpatient claims need a tight tolerance with single-day slop; ER claims sit between. The demo encodes the per-class windows in configuration.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     36[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mDiagnosis concordance is a soft signal.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The diagnoses on the claim and the diagnoses on the EHR encounter overlap but are rarely identical. Treating "diagnoses match exactly" as a required signal will under-link; treating them as completely irrelevant will over-link. The demo scores diagnosis overlap as one feature among several.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     37[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mExternal encounters are first-class outputs.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Many claims do not match any local encounter because the encounter happened elsewhere. These claims are still data; they describe the patient's care trajectory outside the institution. The demo tags them as [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mEXTERNAL_ENCOUNTER[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m and surfaces them for the longitudinal-record-assembler.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     38[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mDynamoDB rejects Python [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mfloat[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;235;203;139m.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Every confidence score, score-breakdown component, and numeric metadata field passes through [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mDecimal[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m on its way in and on its way out. Same gotcha as recipes 5.1 / 5.2 / 5.3 / 5.4 / 5.5; the same [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140m_to_decimal[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m helper handles it.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     39[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe example collapses Step Functions, multiple Glue jobs, multiple Lambdas, and the SQS-driven worker pattern into a single Python file for readability.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m In production the parse-and-normalize, link-patient, cluster-claims, link-encounter, attribute-care-events, persist-and-emit, and invalidate-on-event stages are separate Glue jobs (for batch) and Lambdas (for event-driven slices) orchestrated by Step Functions, each with their own error handling, retries, and DLQs. Comments call out where the boundaries should fall.[K
