[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    2076[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mPhase 2 demonstrates the patient-link review path.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m A claim arrives with a payer-and-member combination that is not in the cross-reference; the matcher routes the claim to the patient-link review queue without attempting encounter-level linking. In production a human reviewer at the eligibility-matching desk resolves the patient identity, the cross-reference table is updated, and the claim re-enters the pipeline.[K
